section.t:
Types will be flagged as obsolete/deprecated in the IANA registry, and the following guidance is given to DNS implementors in the handling of obsolete/deprecated RR types:
Authoritative DNS Servers SHOULD issue a warning when loading zones that contain DEPRECATED RR Types;
DNS Servers MUST NOT compress RDATA when rendering DEPRECATED RR Types to wire format;
Recursive DNS Servers MAY support legacy compression in DEPRECATED RR Types for received data for backward compatibility if desired, but SHOULD warn if such information is received. Compressed RDATA in DEPRECATED RR Types MUST be uncompressed before sending, and MUST NOT be re-transmitted in compressed form;
DNS Clients which receive DEPRECATED RR Types MAY interpret them as unknown RR Types (), and MUST NOT interfere with their transmission;
DNSSEC Validators and Signers SHOULD treat RDATA for DEPRECATED RR Types as opaque with respect to canonical RR ordering and deduplication;
